The paper deals with indexing highly repetitive texts, which is a problem in data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the use of the Burrows-Wheeler Transform (BWT) in indexing, which is a technique commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper proposes new structures and algorithms for text indexing, which falls under distributed computing (cs.DC) and machine learning (cs.LG).
